  "local_port": 38192,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some good libraries in Mumbai?",
  "response": "Mumbai is home to a variety of libraries that cater to different interests, whether you're looking for extensive book collections, historical archives, or serene places to read and study. Here are some of the notable libraries in Mumbai:\n\n### 1. **Asiatic Society of Mumbai**\n- **Location:** Fort, South Mumbai\n- **Highlights:** \n  - One of the oldest libraries in India, established in 1804.\n  - Houses a vast collection of rare manuscripts, books, and artifacts related to Asian history and culture.\n  - Offers research facilities for scholars and enthusiasts.\n  - Stunning colonial architecture and atmospheric reading rooms.\n\n### 2. **RBI Library**\n- **Location:** 6th Floor, Reserve Bank of India Building, Fort, Mumbai\n- **Highlights:** \n  - Managed by the Reserve Bank of India, it primarily serves RBI employees but is also accessible to researchers by appointment.\n  - Extensive collection of books, journals, and research papers on economics, finance, and banking.\n\n### 3. **Jehangir Art Gallery Library**\n- **Location:** Kala Ghoda, South Mumbai\n- **Highlights:** \n  - Focuses on art and culture, housing a range of books on art history, criticism, and contemporary practices.\n  - A perfect spot for artists, students, and art enthusiasts to explore literature related to visual arts.\n\n### 4. **Madras Library**\n- **Location:** Bandra West, Mumbai\n- **Highlights:** \n  - One of Mumbai\u2019s oldest private libraries, founded in 1890.\n  - Collection includes books on literature, history, philosophy, and science.\n  - Offers a quiet environment suitable for reading and studying.\n\n### 5. **The British Centre Library**\n- **Location:** Fort, Mumbai\n- **Highlights:** \n  - Part of the British Council, it provides access to a wide range of books, magazines, and journals.\n  - Focuses on promoting British literature and cultural exchange.\n  - Hosts various events, workshops, and reading programs.\n\n### 6. **Kendriya Vidyalaya Libraries**\n- **Location:** Various branches across Mumbai\n- **Highlights:** \n  - Equipped with well-stocked libraries catering to students from primary to senior levels.\n  - Offers a diverse collection of academic and recreational reading materials.\n  - Access to digital resources and study spaces.\n\n### 7. **University Libraries**\n- **Tata Institute of Social Sciences (TISS) Library**\n  - **Location:** Vile Parle East, Mumbai\n  - **Highlights:** Comprehensive resources on social sciences, humanities, and management.\n  \n- **University of Mumbai Library**\n  - **Location:** Fort, Mumbai\n  - **Highlights:** One of the largest academic libraries in India with extensive collections across various disciplines.\n\n### 8. **Prithvi Theatre Library**\n- **Location:** Juhu, Mumbai\n- **Highlights:** \n  - Specializes in literature related to theater, performing arts, and drama.\n  - Associated with Prithvi Theatre, fostering a community of artists and literature lovers.\n\n### 9. **Pushpa Shetty Memorial Library**\n- **Location:** Andheri East, Mumbai\n- **Highlights:** \n  - Offers a comfortable reading environment with a good selection of books across genres.\n  - Hosts reading sessions and literary events for the community.\n\n### 10. **Online and Digital Libraries**\n- **Wikimedia Library Resources and Digital Initiatives by Local Libraries**\n  - Many Mumbai libraries offer digital catalogs, e-books, and online access to resources.\n  - Useful for those who prefer accessing materials remotely or enhancing their digital research.\n\n---\n\n**Additional Tips:**\n\n- **Membership:** Most libraries require membership or registration to access their full range of services. Check the specific library\u2019s website or contact them directly for membership details.\n  \n- **Timings:** Libraries in Mumbai generally operate from morning to evening, but hours can vary. It\u2019s advisable to verify the timings beforehand.\n\n- **Events and Workshops:** Many libraries host events such as book readings, workshops, seminars, and exhibitions. Keeping an eye on their event calendars can enrich your library experience.\n\nWhether you're a student, researcher, or an avid reader, Mumbai's libraries offer ample resources and tranquil environments to cater to your literary and academic needs.",
